Sentencas: In this work, we report a new design of the contact layer to investigate the significance and mechanism for the cathodic current collection.
Titulo: Mechanism of the cathode current collector on cell performance in a solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: The single cells in a stack are covered with Ag paste on the cathode side, which exhibit slightly higher power density than that of the cell partially covered with Ag paste.
Titulo: Mechanism of the cathode current collector on cell performance in a solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: The Ag paste is applied as a current-collecting layer on the cathode side at the corresponding position in contact with the punctuate structure of the interconnect.
Titulo: Mechanism of the cathode current collector on cell performance in a solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: The difference in power densities between the two single cells is due to the in-plane electron transfer on the cathode surface.
Titulo: Mechanism of the cathode current collector on cell performance in a solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: When the structure of the interconnect is changed from a convex punctuate structure to liner strips, the cell performance is governed by both gas flow rate and in-plane electron transfer; however, the latter plays a more important role than the gas flow rate.
Titulo: Mechanism of the cathode current collector on cell performance in a solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: An appropriate arrangement of current collection at the cathode side is necessary to improve current collection and thus the cell performance inside the SOFC stack.
Titulo: Mechanism of the cathode current collector on cell performance in a solid oxide fuel cell stack
